description:
Honey-lime Chicken And Avocado Salad ğŸ¥— ğŸ¥‘â 
Full recipe below, send to a friend who would love this ğŸ“¤â£â 
ğŸ“¸: Robert Broadfoot, Tastyâ 
â 
Ingredients (for 2 servings)â 
4 boneless chicken thighsâ 
1 head romaine lettuce, choppedâ 
Â½ cup cherry tomato (100 g), halvedâ 
Â½ red onion, thinly slicedâ 
2 avocados, choppedâ 
CHICKEN MARINADEâ 
1 tablespoon olive oilâ 
1 teaspoon saltâ 
2 cloves garlic, mincedâ 
1 jalapeÃ±o pepper, mincedâ 
Â½ teaspoon chili powderâ 
1 tablespoon honeyâ 
4 tablespoons lime juiceâ 
DRESSINGâ 
4 tablespoons olive oilâ 
2 tablespoons honeyâ 
1 teaspoon saltâ 
Â½ teaspoon pepperâ 
4 tablespoons lime juiceâ 
â 
Preparationâ 
In a medium bowl, combine all the ingredients for the chicken marinade.â 
Toss in the chicken thighs and marinate for at least one hour.â 
In a cast-iron skillet, cook chicken on high heat until there is a nice sear on the surface of the chicken, and the inside is no longer pink. Roughly four minutes each side. Set chicken aside.â 
Place chopped lettuce, tomatoes, red onion, and avocados in a large salad bowl.â 
Slice cooked chicken thighs and add to the salad bowl.â 
In a small bowl, combine all the ingredients for the dressing. Mix well.â 
Toss the salad with the dressing and serve immediately.â 
Enjoy!â

description:
My version of beef and potatoes. Made this a while back.  Kabocha pumpkin hashbrowns and topped with @sirkensingtons mayo and sour cream. Omg it was a match made in heaven (not seen in pic bc I forgot to take a pic and ate it too fast ha!) Made Mississippi roast in the crockpot and used Trader Joe's Green Dragon hot sauce. I topped the roast with carmelized onions,  but I ketoized them using coconut aminos instead of soy and a little @lakanto golden sugar. It may not look pretty but the flavors in this meal were delicious ğŸ’¥

description:
Crispy fried Shrimp ğŸ¤ğŸ¤ğŸ¤ In a bowl add 1b shrimp with 1/2 cup all purpose flour, 1/2 cup corn starch, 2 tbsp seasoning sauce (or soy sauce), black pepper, garlic powder, 1 beaten egg and mix well. Add 3/4 cup of Panko bread crumbs and mix well. If you find that the shrimp stick together don't worry about it.
Deep fry. 
I didn't have Sweet chili sauce on hand so I came up with my own sauce.

For the sauce you need

1 tsp chili flakes, 1 tbsp maple syrup,1 tbsp ketchup, 1 tbsp sugar and 1 tbsp vinegar. 
Mix well! Enjoy! :

So you wont be disappointed. I also ordered Pirikara Chicken, which basically everybodyâ€™s favorite ã€Œchicken with hot sauceã€ and Plantain Snack. description: I've been binge-watching @thefoodfreakk on YouTube and I finally put on my big boy pants and decided to cook one of his Roman pastas, pasta alla gricia. description:
Chicken Tray Bake - Chicken & Veggies with Garlic & Thyme 
When itâ€™s a mini celebration of sorts and you want to eat something yummy yet not spend the day in the kitchen - Chicken Tray Bake is the solution. 
I marinated the chicken in the morning and let it freeze in my fridge. Prepped the veggies while the oven preheated and chucked it in the oven about 45mins before dinner time. 
I marinated the skinless chicken legs and the veggies (potatoes, carrots, onions and capsicum) in olive oil, thyme, garlic cloves, paprika, ground pepper and salt. I placed the chicken on the veggies and topped with coriander leaves (couldnâ€™t find parsley) and cooked it in the oven for about 40mins till the juices ran clear, the veggies were soft and roasted and had absorbed all the chicken juices and the chicken had charred well. Served with toasted local bread. 
This was also a big portion for 2 persons so the extra will be shredded chicken and veggies in a sandwich for breakfast or a side for lunch depending on our mood tomorrow morning. .

Ingredients:

-Insert 1-2 chicken pieces into each chili followed by a small quantity of the cheese sauce

ğŸŸ Ikan Cencaru Bakar Sumbat Sambal Kelapa ğŸŸ
.
ğŸŒ¸juliescookingwithluv.blogspot.com
.
Bahan-bahan:-
.
Ikan cencaru 3 ekor
Kelapa parut putih 1 cawan
Cili merah 4 batang
Bawang putih 1 ulas
Serai 1 batang
Bwang merah 5-6 biji
Limau kasturi 4 biji
Gula 1 sudu kecil
Garam secukup rasa
Sedikit minyak untuk menumis
.
Cara-caranya:-
.
Bersihkan ikan cencaru dan kelar di bahagian belakang ikan untuk dijadikan poket.
.
Kisar cili merah, bawang merah, bawang putih dan serai sehingga halus.
.
Tumiskan bahan-bahan yang telah dikisar dengan sedikit minyak.
.
Tumis sehingga bahan-bahana tersebut agak garing. Tambahkan garam dan gula.
.
Kemudian masukkan kelapa parut dan perahan air limau.
.
Gaul semuanya sehingga sebati.
.
Sumbatkan sambal kelapa ke dalam poket ikan. Pastikan padat supaya sambal kelapa tak terkeluar ketika dibakar.
.
Bakar ikan lebih kurang 5 minit setiap bahagian. Aku tak suka kalau ikan bakar kering sangat.

description:
Hi friends ğŸ˜ Salaam to all .Chicken fillets are the heart of chicken shawarma .This is the easiest part in preparing shawarma rolls coz we are going to  just marinate and fry . Let's go to recipe :
CHICKEN MARINATION :
CHICKEN - 250 GRAMS
PEPPER - 1/4 TSP
CHILLI POWDER - 1/4 TSP
GARLIC MINCED- 1 TBSP
CUMIN POWDER - 1/2 TSP
TANDOORI CHICKEN MASALA - 1 TSP
LEMON JUICE - 1 TSP
CINNAMON POWDER - 1/8 TSP
VIRGIN OLIVE OIL - 3 TBSP( 1TBSP GOES FOR MARINATION)
SALT TO TASTE
SHAWARMA ROLL:
ONION FINELY CHOPPED -1/8  CUP
CABBAGE FINELY CHOPPED -1/8 CUP
JULIENNED CARROTS - 1/4 CUP
JULIENNED CAPSICUM -1/4 CUP
JULIENNED TOMATOES -1/4 CUP
ONION SLICED -1/4 CUP
METHOD:
*First slice the boneless chicken in to strips then marinate with the above ingredients .
* Keep aside for 2 hours or refrigerate it .
*Heat oil in skillet, keep in medium flame ,then add the marinated chicken pieces and cook by flipping its sides till they turn brown.If need add more oil while frying it.
* Once the chicken frying part is over ,move on to the shawarma assembling process.
* Mix the finely chopped onion,cabbage to the shawarma sauce .It will  add a crunchiness to sauce (Optional)
*Place a pita bread in a rolling board ,apply 1TBSP of sauce and spread over it ,put chicken fillets ,julienned vegetables and roll it up.
* If u want more saucy add one more layer of sauce above julienned vegetables.
Yayyy!!! Juicy Chicken Shawarma roll is  ready ğŸ˜‹ğŸ˜‹
TIP:
*If u want u can avoid adding julienned vegetables its purely optional
Friends do try tis recipe and comment me how it turned out â˜º

Fry all the flavours (garlic, ginger, mushroom, chilli), set half aside for garnish and add rice to the other half. RECIPE 
Dough for steamed buns/ pau
Pau wheat flour  500g
Instant yeast  8-10g
Warm water  150-200ml
Sugar  1-2 table spoon 
Salt  A bit (optionalï¼‰

For the filling
Depends on what do you like (Char Siu/ pork, chicken, red bean, grated coconut and so on)

INSTRUCTIONS 
1. Prepare ingredients to make the skin of the pau or steamed buns.
2. First, place the pau wheat flour into a mixing bowl.
3. Place the warm water into a glass and add in yeast, sugar and salt, stir well.
4. Combine the yeast mixture with pau wheat flour and knead until the dough is soft, smooth, elastic and does not stick to the sides of the mixing bowl or to your fingers.
5. Cover with a piece of wet cloth and leave to prove until it has doubled its size. I leave it for 45 minutes.
6. Punch down dough to release the air inside, briefly knead again till all is evenly distributed. And you have the basic dough for making pau (buns).
7. Divide the smooth dough in half. Roll into long cylindrical shapes.
8. Cut the dough and shape into balls.
9. Roll each ball into a flat circle with a small rolling pin.
10. Do the same for the rest of the round balls.
11. Have ready the savory any fillings prepared earlier.
12. Spoon in filling into each flattened dough.
13. Gather the edges of the flat dough together.
14. Shape it into pleated pau (bun).
15. Place the pleated pau onto cut parchment or greaseproof paper.
16. Place the pleated pau (buns) onto steaming tray or plate (with holes to allow steam to pass).
17. Leave to prove until double in size, about 15 - 20 minutes.
18. When about time to steam the buns, boil some water in a wok or steamer.
19. Place the buns on steaming tray into the wok.
20. Cover and steam over medium heat for 15 minutes.
21. Transfer steamed buns onto rack to cool before serving. Good luckğŸ˜„

This week we made Chicken Francese and it turned out pretty good! Definitely recommend as a great weeknight dinner ğŸ˜‹

Ingredients:
Chicken:
1/2 cup all-purpose flour.
1 tsp salt or to taste.
1/2 tsp pepper freshly ground, or to taste.
3 large eggs.
1/4 cup vegetable oil.
4 chicken breasts boneless and skinless, thin sliced. -

Sauce.
1 large lemon sliced into thin rounds, seeds removed.
1 cup chicken broth low sodium.
1/2 cup white wine dry.
1 tbsp lemon juice freshly squeezed.
1 tbsp all-purpose flour.
2 tbsp butter unsalted.
2 tbsp parsley chopped, for garnish. -

Instructions:
1. Prepare the flour and eggs: In a shallow plate, add the 1/2 cup of flour, 1 tsp salt and 1/2 tsp of pepper. Whisk to combine. In another shallow plate or bowl whisk the eggs.
2. Dredge the cutlets in the flour mixture, fully coating both sides and shaking off any excess. Next, coat them in the egg mixture.
3. Heat the oil in a large 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat until simmering. Add 3 or 4 pieces of chicken to the skillet (or as many as you can fit). Cook until lightly browned, about 3 minutes per side. Transfer the chicken to a paper towel-lined plate. Repeat with remaining chicken.
4. Make the sauce: Clean the skillet of any excess oil, then add the lemon slices and cook until fragrant and slightly charred, about 30 seconds per side. Add the butter to the skillet and melt it. Whisk in the flour and cook for 30 seconds to cook off the flour taste. Whisk in the wine, broth, lemon juice, and remaining 1/2 teaspoon of salt and season with pepper. Simmer until slightly reduced, about 2 minutes.
5. Finish the dish: Return the chicken to the skillet and cook until for another 3 to 4 minutes. Garnish with the parsley before serving.
-

Tidak terasa sudah dipenghujung Ramadhan. Rasanya cepat sekali Ramadhan meninggalkan kita. Semoga ibadah kita semua diterima oleh-Nya. Aamiin. 
Salah satu takjil favorit saya adalah cendol, sampai saat ini saya suka nyetok tepung cendol dirumah. Jadi kita tinggal memasak dan mencetak saja adonannya. Dulu saya beli alat yang satu paket dengan tepungnya disalah satu TBK di Surabaya. Sebenarnya beberapa kali pernah mencoba eksperimen membuat sendiri adonan cendolnya tapi hasilnya kurang maksimal. Lain kali saya akan coba membuat kembali dan berbagi resepnya kepada teman-teman ya, hehe. 
Nahh.. untuk menambah nilai gizi kali ini saya menambahkan kacang merah seperti permintaan adik saya. Kacang merah kaya akan berbagai nutrisi seperti serat, antioksidan, protein, asam folat, zat besi dan lain sebagainya. Kacang merah ini memiliki indeks glikemik yang rendah sehingga sangat baik untuk penderita diabetes. 
Yukk buat sendiri cendol dirumah. Selamat mencoba teman-teman.. Es Cendol Kacang Merah

Bahan :
1 sachet Tepung cendol siap pakai 
100 gram Nangka, potong dadu kecil
500 ml Santan kental, rebus dengan daun pandan dan sedikit garam
250 gram Gula merah, rebus dengan sedikit air dan daun pandan
Es batu secukupnya

200 gram Kacang merah, rendam semalaman
75 gram Gula kelapa
Air secukupnya
Daun pandan 
Cara membuat :
1. Siapkan panci rebus kacang merah bersama gula kelapa dan daun pandan hingga lunak. Sisihkan.
2. Buat adonan cendol sesuai instruksi pada kemasan. Lalu cetak menggunakan Catalan cendol pada air es. Sisihkan.
3. Ambil gelas saji, beri es batu, gula merah cair, santan, cendol, kacang merah dan yang terakhir potongan nangka. Sajikan. 
Teman-teman dapat menambahkan buah durian jika suka.

PUMPKIN MUFFINSğŸ¤¤ğŸ¤¤
{gluten free + dairy free + refined sugar free + lowfodmap}
â €
this is seriously one of the best recipes iâ€™ve ever made. muffin texture is so fluffy & so moist itâ€™s unreal that theyâ€™re gf, df & full of healthier ingredients. I promise u wonâ€™t be disappointedğŸ¤©
â €
_________________________________
âœï¸Recipe: about 12 muffins
>INGREDIENTS
* 1 1/2 c @bobsredmill 1-to-1 gf flour
* 1 tsp baking powder
* 1 tsp baking soda
* 1/2 tsp salt
* 2.5 tsp @mccormickspice cinnamon
* 2 @vitalfarms eggs
* 1/4 c @thefreshmarket 100% maple syrup
* 1/2 c @carringtonfarms coconut oil
* 1/2 can (1 c) @traderjoes canned pumpkin
* sweetener (optional but recommended if you like sweetness. I used 1/2 tsp of stevia extract powder which was = to 1/4 c sugar for reference, I would do at least 1 tsp if u want it more like dessert!)
â €
>DIRECTIONS
-Preheat oven to 350F.
-Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt & cinnamon.
-In separate large bowl, beat eggs until combined.
-While beating, add in oil & maple syrup.
-With mixer at low speed, add sifted dry ingredients alternatively with pumpkin, begin & end this with dry ingredients. Beat until smooth between each addition.
-Pour into lightly greased muffin tin (about 12 muffins). I topped mine with a few walnuts.
-Bake for 20-25 minutes.

description:
Once in a while I used to get lunch from this Hawaiian Korean fusion restaurant close to my work. My go to was their kimchi fried rice with chicken, and a sunny side up egg! I was craving that for soooo long, and finally decided to give it a try. Iâ€™m pleasantly surprised how delicious this turned out to be! And also looks gorgeous! Probably not the most authentic, but hereâ€™s the recipe, and it barely took 30 minutes to make:
1. Season 1lb of shrimp with salt, a pinch of turmeric and 1tsp of ground black pepper
2. Heat 1tbsp of oil in a deep pan or wok, cook the shrimp for about 2 minutes and set aside
3. In the same pan, add another 1tbsp of oil, and saute 1cup of chopped onions, 1tbsp of minced garlic. 
4. Once thoroughly cooked, add 1 cup of drained kimchi and 1tbsp of gochujang paste, cook for about 2-3 minutes.
5. Add the kimchi juice, 2tsps of soy sauce and 2tsps of fish sauce and cook for another 1 minute.
6. Add 2 cups of cooked day-old rice, and mix really well. Cook for 3-4 minutes
7. Move all the rice to a side, and crack 2 eggs on the other side, cook until itâ€™s set and season with salt and pepper. Scramble the eggs and combine with the rice really well.
8. Add the cooked shrimp at this point and cook for a minute.
9. Squeeze half a lemon and throw in some chopped scallions and give it a good mix.
10. Serve with a sunny side up egg!

description:
#Repost from @helenysm_ (@repost_media_app)
Frozen Pork Noodles!
Praktis dan nikmat buat sarapan.

Buat kalian yang suka bingung, mau sarapan apa, sementara sekarang ribet beli-beli di luar. Mending stok aja Frozen Noodles di rumah, jadinya kapanpun bisa nge-yamien.

Bakmi Asia punya aneka macam Frozen Pork Noodles, dengan beberapa pilihan homemade noodle seperti: mie biasa dan mie gepeng, ada juga mie hijau yang terbuat dari poleng/caisim. Bisa pilih juga  mau pakai baso atau pangsit. Pokoknya sesuai selera masing-masing deh.

Frozen Pork Noodles ini sudah komplit termasuk topping babi kecap cincang, ayam suwir, bawang goreng dan sambal. Pokoknya tinggal dimasak bentar, langsung enak deh.

Yuk borong buat stok #dirumahaja.

Bakmi Asia

Savoury Vegan Bowl ğŸ¥‘ğŸ¥—
â—†Ingredientsâ—†
â—olive oil
â—a bunch of cherry tomatoes on the vine
â—250 g / 9 oz cooked and cooled small potatoes, halved
â— salt to taste
â— black pepper, to taste
â—100 g / 3.5 oz baby spinach
â— 1 large shallot, finely diced
â— 1 garlic clove, finely diced
â—300 g / 10.5 oz silken firm tofu (I useÂ Clearspring)
â—Â¼ tsp turmeric, adjust to taste
â—Â¼ tspÂ black saltÂ (has eggy taste), adjust to taste
â—Â½ ripe avocado, cut in half

Methods:
â— Brush tomatoes with a little oil (keeping them on the vine if you can) and place them on a small baking tray. Stick them under a grill / broiler for 5-10 minutes, until their skins burst and the tops char a little. Season and set aside. â— Heat up 2 tsp of olive oil on a small frying pan. Place cold potatoes, cut side down on the hot oil and allow them to fry gently until nicely browned. Season with salt and pepper. â— Place spinach on another pan with a splash of water. Allow the spinach to wilt using gentle heat. Move it around the pan with a pair of tongs. Season and lift wilted spinach out of the pan, draining any excess water away. â— Heat up a tablespoon of oil in a pan (I reused the one I used to wilt the spinach) and fry diced shallot and garlic on a very gentle heat. â—Once shallot is translucent and garlic fragrant (but not browned), add the drained tofu. Smash it a little with the back of a spoon. Season with turmeric, black salt (it will give it eggy taste) and pepper. â— Divide all the elements (including the avocado) between two bowls and drizzle with extra olive oil if needed.

Honey-lime Chicken And Avocado Salad ğŸ¥— ğŸ¥‘â 
Full recipe below, send to a friend who would love this ğŸ“¤â£â 
ğŸ“¸: Robert Broadfoot, Tastyâ 
â 
Ingredients (for 2 servings)â 
4 boneless chicken thighsâ 
1 head romaine lettuce, choppedâ 
Â½ cup cherry tomato (100 g), halvedâ 
Â½ red onion, thinly slicedâ 
2 avocados, choppedâ 
CHICKEN MARINADEâ 
1 tablespoon olive oilâ 
1 teaspoon saltâ 
2 cloves garlic, mincedâ 
1 jalapeÃ±o pepper, mincedâ 
Â½ teaspoon chili powderâ 
1 tablespoon honeyâ 
4 tablespoons lime juiceâ 
DRESSINGâ 
4 tablespoons olive oilâ 
2 tablespoons honeyâ 
1 teaspoon saltâ 
Â½ teaspoon pepperâ 
4 tablespoons lime juiceâ 
â 
Preparationâ 
In a medium bowl, combine all the ingredients for the chicken marinade.â 
Toss in the chicken thighs and marinate for at least one hour.â 
In a cast-iron skillet, cook chicken on high heat until there is a nice sear on the surface of the chicken, and the inside is no longer pink. Roughly four minutes each side. Set chicken aside.â 
Place chopped lettuce, tomatoes, red onion, and avocados in a large salad bowl.â 
Slice cooked chicken thighs and add to the salad bowl.â 
In a small bowl, combine all the ingredients for the dressing. Mix well.â 
Toss the salad with the dressing and serve immediately.â 
Enjoy!â

Dessert yang bikin adem dan ngangenin, salah satu comfort food saya nih.

Tersedia 6 varian rasa: Marie, Lotus, Dalgona, Choco, Jasmine, dan Oreo, semuanya istimewa. Saya sih demen banget sama saus/vla nya, jadi untuk setiap varian, selain ada tambahan saus, ada juga yang plus topping crunchynya. Ahhh.. love bangetlah!

Tersedia pula kemasan box eksklusif khusus untuk Eid Mubarak Hampers. Wah  cantik, keren, dan enak buat meramaikan Hari Raya nih, buruan pesan sekarang juga.

ThattaiÂ is a south Indian deep fried tea time snack made withÂ riceflour & commonly prepared during Janmashtami or Sri Krishna Jayanthi festival. This preparation has salted and sweet versions. It is known as "Nippattu" in Karnataka and "Chekkalu" in Andhra Pradesh/Telangana.

.

.
.
.
.
So tried this new recipe of thattai made out of rice flour, urad dal, channa dal which was flavoured with curry leaf, red chilli, asafoetida.
Soaked channa dal added to the mixture of rice flour,redchilli, curry leaves & asafoetida which is then mixed into a dough later on making it into a flat bread shape & deep fried in oil. The written process seems simple but there is little work to do.

* @thefreshmarket shrimp

* spoonful of my homemade pestoğŸ‘‡ğŸ¼

âœï¸Pesto Recipe: makes a few servings
>INGREDIENTS
* 1/2 c basil
* 1/2 c spinach (or another green)
* 1/4 c arugula
* 1/2 c pine nuts
* 3 tbsp lemon juice
* 3 tbsp nutritional yeast
* 1/4 c olive oil
* lots of salt & pepper as needed
â €
>DIRECTIONS
-Place all ingredients in food processor & blend until combined. Can taste it & add more of anything if needed.
** I like to make this whole batch then freeze it for future meals. If you have an ice cube tray you can make ice cubes with this then keep in a freezer bag & take out cubes to melt on pan when needed; super easy! **

description:
Frozen Pork Noodles!
Praktis dan nikmat buat sarapan.

Buat kalian yang suka bingung, mau sarapan apa, sementara sekarang ribet beli-beli di luar. Mending stok aja Frozen Noodles di rumah, jadinya kapanpun bisa nge-yamien.

Bakmi Asia punya aneka macam Frozen Pork Noodles, dengan beberapa pilihan homemade noodle seperti: mie biasa dan mie gepeng, ada juga mie hijau yang terbuat dari poleng/caisim. Bisa pilih juga  mau pakai baso atau pangsit. Pokoknya sesuai selera masing-masing deh.

Frozen Pork Noodles ini sudah komplit termasuk topping babi kecap cincang, ayam suwir, bawang goreng dan sambal. Pokoknya tinggal dimasak bentar, langsung enak deh.

Yuk borong buat stok #dirumahaja.

Bakmi Asia

description:
PeshwaÂ Baji Rao I, prime minister toÂ Chattrapati Shahu, laid the ceremonial foundation of his own residence on Saturday, 10 January 1730. It was namedÂ Shaniwarwadafrom the Marathi wordsÂ ShaniwarÂ (Saturday) andÂ WadaÂ (a general term for any residence complex).Â TeakÂ was imported from the jungles ofÂ Junnar, stone was brought from the nearby quarries ofÂ Chinchwad, andÂ Lime (mineral)was brought from the lime-belts ofÂ Jejuri. Shaniwarwada was completed in 1732, at a total cost of Rs. 16,110, a very large sum at that time.

The opening ceremony was performed according to religious customs, on 22 January 1732, another Saturday chosen for being a particularly auspicious day.

Later the Peshwas made several additions, including the fortification walls, with bastions and gates; court halls and other buildings; fountains and reservoirs. Currently, the perimeter fortification wall has five gateways and nine bastion towers, enclosing a garden complex with the foundations of the original buildings. It is situated near theÂ Mula-Mutha River, inÂ Kasba Peth.

description:
Spike Speigel - from Cowboy Bebop - arguably the best character in Anime history - voiced by the legendary @blumspew who had a birthday the other day - Happy belated birthday sir. I'm excited to see the live-action series coming to Netflix and I'm especially excited to see what @johnthecho does with the role of Spike.

The show itself has been heavily influential on my life - I first saw shortly after my parents' divorce and even though I didn't know it at the time - it's a show about letting go. It also genre hops with each episode and with the music, plus the animation is just top-notch. It's timeless, it's complete and it all started from a toy spaceship contract with Bandai and it's very gifted Director @shinichiro_watanabe

Anywho this was a sharpie doodle - and I took it into photoshop for a really basic coloring session. Enjoy.

description:
MATI GAYA KELAMAAN WFH

Anak-anak saya termasuk dalam kategori pahlawan dimasa Pandemi ini.. Kerjaannya di dominasi oleh aktivitas "rebahan." Memang kadang ada kuliah/kelas online dan olahraga-diet. Tapi utamanya tetap saja rebahan.

Saking sudah lamanya WFH/SFH, mereka mulai mati gaya karena tidak punya foto baru untuk di upload di media sosial mereka. Makanya hari ini anak wedok tiba-tiba masuk kamar saya saat saya sedang ngobrol sama Bojo dan bilang minta tolong fotoin dan juga sudah dandan. Ini berarti agak serius untuk buat foto baru. Dapar order motret anak wedok, bapaknya age-age gresek-gresek ambil camera, langsung mangkat menyang... Anak millenials kalau berpose selalu punya gaya standar. Lidah nya melet ğŸ˜‚... Ini tentu saja diluar selera fotografi bapaknya. Makanya bapaknya nunggu momen saat anak wedok mbenerin pose, langsung jepret, candid. Jadinya adalah foto ini... Bapaknya happy melihat hasilnya. Setelah foto di share, anak wedok juga happy karena dalam sejam di upload, sudah ada ratusan yang nge-like.

Melihat hasil foto anak wedok, Bojo saya jadi juga kepingin di foto. Tentu saja saya juga age-age mau motret bojo... Tapi bojo ternyata punya target pra-kondisi... "Aku di foto ya... Tapi nanti kalau sudah kurus..." Wah lha kalau prakondisi yang di syaratkan itu adalah "kurus", ya nggak akan kelakon fotonya... ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ #kurusiturelatif

description:
Constant Variable : 136/366 Days Portrait 
Title: Bi-Lingual
15-05-2020
Pen on paper 11"x14"
The Jain philosophical doctrine 'Anekantvada' forms the basis of my interdisciplinary practice. The doctrine states that all entities have three aspects: substance (dravya), quality (guna) and mode (paryaya), and each of them is constantly undergoing transformation and modification. These elements make perception of reality difficult to assess from one one point of view. Each view-point yields, different conclusion. The nature of reality is expressed completely none of them but by all of them together. 
The only constant in my life for past 10 years has been @jeysushil . This art project titled- 'Constant Variable' is an ambitious act of analysing one subject over 366 days' through as many portraits.

description:
Mindfulness is our natural quality but most of us have lost it in our busy lives which usually is on autopilot mode. In simple words mindfulness can also be explained as simply trying to bring our attention to the present moment and that too without judgement. It can be practiced either as a form of mindfulness meditation or by focusing on simple everyday activities like eating or breathing. The key word is 'without any Judgement.' We have to try to quieten the inner critic in our heads while paying attention and if we start to judge, then we make a mental note of it and let it pass. It's about living in the moment, being present and returning to the present moment again and again. Mindfulness has a lot of scientifically proven benefits which I will share in my next post. Stay safe everyone and Happy Weekend..

description:
Jumping Frogs

The Story:

A group of frogs was hopping through the forest when two of them accidentally hopped into a deep pit. The other frogs stood around the pit, and, seeing how deep it was, they told the two frogs that they couldnâ€™t help themâ€“there was no hope.

However, fighting for their lives, the two frogs ignored the others and started to try jumping out of the pit.

The frogs at the top continued to tell the frogs in the pit to give up, as there was no way they would be able to jump out.

After trying over and over, one of the frogs listened to the others and gave up, accepting his fate and falling to his death. But the other frog continued to jump with all of his might. The crowd of frogs yelled down the pit for the frog to just stopâ€“he wouldnâ€™t make it.

But the frog jumped even harder and persisted until he finally got out. Upon reaching the top, the other frogs said, â€œWe thought there was no way any frog could jump that highâ€“couldnâ€™t you hear us?â€ The frog then signaled to the others that he was deaf, and he thought that the frogs standing around the pit were encouraging him the whole time.

The Moral:

Othersâ€™ words can greatly impact your attitude and actions. Ignore the naysayers. Only engage with thoseÂ who encourage youÂ and believe in your ability to succeed. Furthermore, think about what you say to people before speaking so you can make sure what youâ€™re saying is supportive. Your support (or lack thereof) could make the difference between success and failure .
